P({\rm failure}) = P(Y(2) = 1) = P(\{Y(1)=1,Y(2) = 1\} \cup \{Y(1) = 0, Y(2) = 1\})
\qquad = P(\{Y(1)=1,Y(2) = 1\} ) + P( \{Y(1) = 0, Y(2) = 1\}) \quad {\rm (disjoint)}
\qquad = P(Y(2) = 1 |  Y(1) = 1)P(Y(1) = 1) + P(  Y(2) = 1 | Y(1) = 0)P(Y(1) = 0) \quad {\rm (conditional probability)}
\qquad = 1* 0.7 +0.91*0.3. 
